# Validator Behavioral Contract — Rocq aggregation (Workstream E, stage E5)
#
# This project NAMES the built-in validator's behavioral contract. It does
# NOT re-prove anything: each `validator_contract_*` theorem in
# theories/Contract.v is a definitional alias (`:=`) of an obligation that is
# ALREADY proven, kernel-checked, and axiom-free in the CostAccountedRho and
# Slashing developments. Naming the obligations here gives a single Rocq
# surface a custom validator (or a reviewer) can point at as "the contract",
# mirroring the Lean surface in formal/lean/Validator/Contract.lean and the
# TLA+ surface in formal/tlaplus/validator/Validator.tla.
#
# Because every clause is a `:=` alias, its kernel footprint is identical to
# the underlying obligation; `Print Assumptions validator_contract_X` reports
# exactly what `Print Assumptions <obligation>` reports — "Closed under the
# global context" for all seven, so the axiom gate validates these clauses
# just as it does the obligations they re-export.
#
# Contract <-> obligation <-> spec map (full table in
# docs/theory/cost-accounting-impl/, also reproduced in Contract.v):
#   S1  token-present / reject-malformed   §6.3   <- FuelGateSafety
#   S2  accept iff Σ_s ≥ Δ_s (decidable)   §7.6   <- LinearLogicResources
#   S3  linear no-double-spend             §7.7   <- LinearLogicResources
#   S4  for-comp = atomic funded txn       §7.1   <- StepDeterminism
#   P1  slash-authorization soundness      DR-12  <- MainTheorem / Validator (Slashing)
#   P2  fork-choice exclusion of slashed   DR-12  <- MainTheorem (Slashing)
#   P3  determinism / replay-equivalence   DR-12  <- StepDeterminism (== S4)
#
# The validator project depends on BOTH already-compiled developments. Their
# .vo files must exist first (the cost_accounted_rho and slashing projects
# compile independently via their own `rocq makefile -f _CoqProject`). The two
# logical roots load together with no namespace or universe conflict (verified:
# the Slashing `Validator` record and the CostAccountedRho process syntax
# coexist cleanly).

-Q ../cost_accounted_rho/theories CostAccountedRho
-Q ../slashing/theories Slashing
-Q theories Validator

theories/Contract.v
